#: oral-goal-oriented-co-operation-en.txt:2
msgid ""
"Goal-oriented co-operation (cooking together, discussing a document, "
"organising an event, etc.)"
msgstr ""

#: oral-goal-oriented-co-operation-en.txt:4
msgid "C2_No descriptors available; see C1"
msgstr ""

#: oral-goal-oriented-co-operation-en.txt:6
msgid ""
"C1_Can frame a discussion to decide on a course of action with a partner or "
"group, reporting on what others have said, and summarising, elaborating and "
"weighing up multiple points of view."
msgstr ""

#: oral-goal-oriented-co-operation-en.txt:10
msgid ""
"B2_Can understand detailed instructions reliably."
"Can help along the progress of the work by inviting others to join in, "
"express what they think, etc."
"Can outline an issue or a problem clearly, speculating about causes or "
"consequences, and weighing advantages and disadvantages of different "
"approaches."
msgstr ""

#: oral-goal-oriented-co-operation-en.txt:14
msgid ""
"B1+_Can follow what is said, though they may occasionally have to ask for "
"repetition or clarification if the discussion is rapid or extended."
"Can explain why something is a problem, discuss what to do next, and compare "
"and contrast alternatives."
"Can give brief comments on the views of others."
msgstr ""

#: oral-goal-oriented-co-operation-en.txt:18
msgid ""
"B1_Can generally follow what is said and, when necessary, repeat back part "
"of what someone has said to confirm mutual understanding."
"Can make their opinions and reactions understood as regards possible "
"solutions or the question of what to do next, giving brief reasons and "
"explanations."
"Can invite others to give their views on how to proceed."
msgstr ""

#: oral-goal-oriented-co-operation-en.txt:21
msgid ""
"A2+_Can understand enough to manage simple, routine tasks without undue "
"effort, asking very simply for repetition when they do not understand."
"Can discuss what to do next, making and responding to suggestions, and "
"asking for and giving directions."
msgstr ""

#: oral-goal-oriented-co-operation-en.txt:24
msgid ""
"A2_Can indicate when they are following and can be made to understand what "
"is necessary, if the interlocutor takes the trouble."
"Can communicate in simple and routine tasks using simple phrases to ask for "
"and provide things, to get simple information and to discuss what to do next."
msgstr ""

#: oral-goal-oriented-co-operation-en.txt:28
msgid ""
"A1_Can understand questions and instructions addressed carefully and slowly "
"to them and follow short, simple directions."
"Can act on basic instructions that involve times, locations, numbers, etc."
"Can ask people for things, and give people things."
msgstr ""

